\f0\fs28 \cf2 \'93In library and recordkeeping practice we are moving rapidly from collection-based models, whose principles and practices have been developed over many centuries, to models where collections are not of paramount importance and where what matters is the extent of access provided to information resources\'94 (Harvey p10)}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1265\cocoasubrtf190
{\fonttbl\f0\fnil\fcharset0 National-Book;}
