\f0\fs28 \cf2 \'93The phrase benign neglect provides an example of a concept that is helpful in the pre-digital preservation paradigm but is harmful in the new. It refers to the concept that many informa- tion carriers made of organic materials (most notably paper-based artifacts) will not deteriorate rapidly if they are left undisturbed. For digital materials this concept is positively harmful.\'94 (Harvey p. ~11)}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1265\cocoasubrtf190
{\fonttbl\f0\fnil\fcharset0 National-Book;}
{\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;\red255\green248\blue228;}
