\f0\fs28 \cf2 \'93Definitions of preservation provided by survey re- spondents, Cloonan and Sanett (2002, p.85) concluded, \'91demonstrate a shift taking place from defining preservation as a once-and-forever approach for paper-based materials, to an all-the-time approach for digital materials\'92. This shift implies an acceptance that preservation may even begin before a record has been created.\'94 (Harvey)}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1265\cocoasubrtf190
{\fonttbl\f0\fnil\fcharset0 National-Book;}
