\f0\fs28 \cf2 [Harvey p. 50ish\} processable units \'85 according to the logic of some application software. The rules that govern the logical object are independent of how the data are written on a physical medium \'85 A logical unit is a unit recognized by some application software. This rec- ognition is typically based on data type [for example, ASCII or other more complex formats] \'85 to preserve digital information as logical objects, we have to know the requirements for correct processing of each object\'92s data type and what software can perform correct processing (Thibodeau, 2002, p.7).}

