\f0\fs28 \cf2 \'93No. All archives are records, but not all records become archives. Government agencies, individuals and organisations create and accumulate records\'85. Many of these records are destroyed once their usefulness for current purposes ceases. Those that are preserved because of their enduring value are called archives.\'94 (National archives of Australia, Fact sheet 4, March 2000, cited in Cork 2000)}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1265\cocoasubrtf190
{\fonttbl\f0\fnil\fcharset0 National-Book;}
{\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;\red255\green248\blue228;}
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\pardirnatural

\f0\fs28 \cf2 Datajournalism: storing data visualisations and interactive journalism pieces is important but harder than textual articles}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1265\cocoasubrtf190
{\fonttbl\f0\fnil\fcharset0 National-Book;}
{\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;\red255\green248\blue228;}
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\pardirnatural

\f0\fs28 \cf2 \'93Librarians manage hybrid libraries, consisting of both physical collections and distributed digital information resources, and digital libraries. Other stakeholders with a keen inter- est in digital preservation manage digital information in specific subject areas, such as geospatial data or social science data. In the past this material, where it existed, was maintained as collections of paper and other physical objects. The practices developed and applied in libraries and archives are still largely based on managing physical collections and cannot be applied automatically to managing digital collections.\'94 (Harvey)}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1265\cocoasubrtf190
{\fonttbl\f0\fnil\fcharset0 National-Book;}
{\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;\red255\green248\blue228;}
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\pardirnatural

\f0\fs28 \cf2 For how long? -> there is not an immediate need to preserve your data for more than your lifetime + your children\'92s. There is a need to be selective in the data preservation - some might be valuable for others, some is only backup for your own use}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1265\cocoasubrtf190
{\fonttbl\f0\fnil\fcharset0 National-Book;}
{\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;\red255\green248\blue228;}
