\f0\fs28 \cf2 \'93people will want to use the best available technol- ogy\'97or at least technologies they know how to use\'97for discovery, retrieval, processing, and delivery of preserved information. There is a danger that to the degree that preservation solutions keep things unaltered they will create barriers to satisfying this basic user requirement.\'94 (thibodeau 2002 conclusion p 28)}

