\f0\fs28 \cf2 \'93Without reliable evidence set in context, to be sure memory becomes counterfeit, or at least is transformed into forgery, manipulation, or imagination. Without the influence of and need for memory, evidence is useless and unused. Without acknowledging the mediation and intervention of the archivist in the construction of memory based on documentary evidence, the claims for that evidence of impartiality, objectivity, and \'93Truth\'94 ring hollow at best, as professional arrogance at worst.\'94 (Cook 2000)}

