\f0\fs28 \cf2 Michael Zimmer \'93This is the classic \'93but the information is already public\'94 argument that, while technically true, presumes a false dichotomy that information is either strictly public or private, ignoring any contextual norms that might have guided the initial release of information or how a person expects that information to flow.\'94 [Information is not an object but a statement; it goes through socio-technical processes; it doesn\'92t have an objective nature] CPB 2010. Zimmer on dev lists {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://listserv.aoir.org/pipermail/air-l-aoir.org/2010-April/021136.html%5D"}}{\fldrslt http://listserv.aoir.org/pipermail/air-l-aoir.org/2010-April/021136.html]}}}

